# Testing Rules

## Framework

- pytest with `pytest-cov` for coverage
- `httpx.AsyncClient` for FastAPI integration tests
- `pytest-asyncio` with `asyncio_mode = "auto"` (set in pyproject.toml)

## Structure

```
tests/
├── conftest.py          Shared fixtures (app client, settings overrides)
├── test_retrieval.py    Retrieval pipeline tests
├── test_cache.py        Semantic cache tests
└── test_routing.py      Query routing tests
```

## Rules

- Each test function tests exactly one behaviour
- Test names: `test_<what>_<condition>_<expected_result>`
- Use real services where fast; mock only external HTTP calls and LLM APIs
- Every new feature needs at least one happy-path and one error-path test
- Target: >80% coverage on `app/`

## Running Tests

```bash
uv run pytest                          # all tests
uv run pytest tests/test_retrieval.py  # single file
uv run pytest --cov=app --cov-report=term-missing
```
